<i>♪ Back up ♪</i>

24
00:00:53,505 --> 00:00:55,661
- ♪ So what? ♪
- Ugh.

25
00:00:55,743 --> 00:00:56,925
- Nope.
- Hmm?

26
00:00:57,002 --> 00:00:58,169
- Kids live here now.
- Oh.

27
00:00:58,246 --> 00:00:59,348
Oh, okay, bedroom,

28
00:00:59,425 --> 00:01:01,740
- bedroom. Ah!
- Okay. Good idea.

29
00:01:02,707 --> 00:01:04,436
- Betty's still awake.
- Oh.

30
00:01:04,513 --> 00:01:06,732
Oh, and so is Leo.

31
00:01:06,837 --> 00:01:07,954
Okay, I'll just, uh...

32
00:01:08,031 --> 00:01:10,098
Our brains and bodies
are actually programmed

33
00:01:10,175 --> 00:01:11,768
to seek each other out
and connect.

34
00:01:11,845 --> 00:01:14,142
- <i>♪ Da, ba-da-ba-da-da ♪
- ♪ Whoo! ♪</i>

35
00:01:14,219 --> 00:01:17,187
So, then why do so many people
prefer being alone?

36
00:01:17,264 --> 00:01:19,177
Have you been
home all night?

37
00:01:19,343 --> 00:01:21,044
I just got here.

38
00:01:21,900 --> 00:01:24,430
Do you dream vividly?

39
00:01:24,507 --> 00:01:27,187
Like, so vivid, you can feel
how the dream felt

40
00:01:27,264 --> 00:01:28,840
in your whole body?

41
00:01:28,917 --> 00:01:29,976
What's with all the milk?

42
00:01:30,053 --> 00:01:32,638
I almost slept
with Owen.

43
00:01:33,517 --> 00:01:35,010
- So, you bought milk?
- No.

44
00:01:35,087 --> 00:01:36,840
The baby woke up,
it was awkward,

45
00:01:36,917 --> 00:01:38,636
so I came over here
to get clothes.

46
00:01:38,713 --> 00:01:39,804
Why is everyone awake?

47
00:01:39,881 --> 00:01:40,840
Uh...

48
00:01:40,917 --> 00:01:42,067
Jackson proposed.

49
00:01:42,144 --> 00:01:43,990
- With milk?
- Wait, what?

50
00:01:44,327 --> 00:01:46,544
Or half-proposed.

51
00:01:46,648 --> 00:01:48,538
He was not not talking
about marriage.

52
00:01:48,615 --> 00:01:51,497
Is he competing with April?
I kind of get that.

53
00:01:51,583 --> 00:01:53,093
What did you say?

54
00:01:53,170 --> 00:01:56,974
I said that, um,
I had to go get some milk.

55
00:01:57,064 --> 00:01:58,251
And what did he say?

56
00:01:58,328 --> 00:02:00,260
I don't know.
I left to get the milk.

57
00:02:00,337 --> 00:02:02,562
You know, he probably
doesn't really believe

58
00:02:02,639 --> 00:02:03,639
that you needed it.

59
00:02:03,716 --> 00:02:05,260
I had to get it, Meredith.

60
00:02:05,337 --> 00:02:07,640
Okay, well, why don't you
just tell Jackson

61
00:02:07,717 --> 00:02:09,058
that you're not ready?

62
00:02:09,135 --> 00:02:10,345
No.

63
00:02:11,087 --> 00:02:12,680
You are ready?
No!

64
00:02:12,757 --> 00:02:14,768
No, we haven't even said
"I love you" yet.

65
00:02:14,845 --> 00:02:16,779
It is too soon.
It...

66
00:02:17,047 --> 00:02:19,022
It's like you and Owen
playing house.

67
00:02:19,099 --> 00:02:21,888
Like insta-family,
like you just get a cup of soup,

68
00:02:21,965 --> 00:02:24,138
add some water,
and bam, family.

69
00:02:24,215 --> 00:02:25,786
At least until...

70
00:02:26,126 --> 00:02:27,495
Until what?

71
00:02:30,728 --> 00:02:32,263
We need toilet paper.

72
00:02:43,757 --> 00:02:45,985
Hey, I'm not entirely sure
why you left,

73
00:02:46,062 --> 00:02:47,109
but I'm back
at the hospital.

74
00:02:47,186 --> 00:02:49,268
My patient spiked
a post-op fever.

75
00:02:49,345 --> 00:02:50,964
So, call me back, okay?

76
00:02:51,041 --> 00:02:52,110
Is she okay?

77
00:02:52,187 --> 00:02:54,018
Just lay back, Ms.
Colvin. Try to relax.

78
00:02:54,095 --> 00:02:55,198
She's been in and out
since you left,

79
00:02:55,275 --> 00:02:56,142
and her blood pressure's
dropping.

80
00:02:56,219 --> 00:02:57,219
All right.
Let's get a sepsis work-up,

81
00:02:57,296 --> 00:02:58,626
a chest X-ray,
and some cultures.

82
00:02:58,703 --> 00:02:59,875
Blood and urine
is already done.

83
00:02:59,952 --> 00:03:02,339
Hey, Nisha, I'm gonna check out
your back, all right?

84
00:03:02,416 --> 00:03:03,523
It might sting
a little bit.

85
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:05,472
Nisha, how you feeling?

86
00:03:05,549 --> 00:03:06,566
I don't know.

87
00:03:06,643 --> 00:03:07,902
How am I feeling?

88
00:03:07,979 --> 00:03:09,398
You got a bit
of an infection back here,

89
00:03:09,475 --> 00:03:11,515
but I'm gonna change up
your antibiotics, okay?

90
00:03:11,592 --> 00:03:14,355
You can do
whatever you want to me.

91
00:03:14,432 --> 00:03:16,354
See?
I flirted!

92
00:03:16,431 --> 00:03:17,812
Excellent work.

93
00:03:17,889 --> 00:03:20,999
A little aggressive,
but once the drugs wear off,

94
00:03:21,076 --> 00:03:23,154
we'll work on the nuance.

95
00:03:25,316 --> 00:03:27,085
She's in V-Tach!
Pull in the crash cart!

96
00:03:27,162 --> 00:03:28,414
What's happening?

97
00:03:28,491 --> 00:03:31,161
Paddles.
Sync charge to 100.

98
00:03:32,349 --> 00:03:33,362
All right, here we go.

99
00:03:33,439 --> 00:03:34,896
We got you.

100
00:03:36,434 --> 00:03:37,549
Clear!

101
00:03:38,080 --> 00:03:39,149
Still V-Tach.

102
00:03:39,226 --> 00:03:41,182
- Help her, please!
- 120.

103
00:03:41,366 --> 00:03:43,037
- Clear.
- Help her!

104
00:03:43,114 --> 00:03:44,608
- You have to do something!
- 200.

105
00:03:44,685 --> 00:03:45,882
Clear.

106
00:03:48,519 --> 00:03:50,265
What... What happened?

107
00:03:50,342 --> 00:03:52,125
Dr. Avery,
her heart rate's climbing.

108
00:03:52,202 --> 00:03:53,555
Ah, it's gonna be
a long night.

109
00:03:53,632 --> 00:03:54,948
Here we go.

